{"type":"user.message","data":{"content":"I'm writing MSTest tests for a factory method. Is there a better MSTest assertion to check the returned type instead of hard casting?\n\n```csharp\n[TestMethod]\npublic void Create_ReturnsCorrectHandler()\n{\n    var factory = new HandlerFactory();\n    var result = factory.Create(\"email\");\n\n    var handler = (EmailHandler)result;\n    Assert.IsNotNull(handler);\n    Assert.AreEqual(\"email\", handler.Type);\n}\n```\n","transformedContent":"<current_datetime>2026-05-13T10:10:29.479Z</current_datetime>\n\nI'm writing MSTest tests for a factory method. Is there a better MSTest assertion to check the returned type instead of hard casting?\n\n```csharp\n[TestMethod]\npublic void Create_ReturnsCorrectHandler()\n{\n    var factory = new HandlerFactory();\n    var result = factory.Create(\"email\");\n\n    var handler = (EmailHandler)result;\n    Assert.IsNotNull(handler);\n    Assert.AreEqual(\"email\", handler.Type);\n}\n```","attachments":[],"interactionId":"28e76f7a-2677-49ff-bef8-15a2347d97e6"},"id":"b3833375-8ee1-4d15-9ba7-68e972873a1e","timestamp":"2026-05-13T10:10:29.479Z","parentId":"02543cbb-20a9-4aee-8f95-846abd3d2a13"}
